            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Newark.</placeName>
                    <date>Oct 29<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>/68.</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am very sorry to have troubled you again to write to me, I should have sent you the averages sooner if possible, but I have only today finished making them out.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>On the other side I send a list of male and female lambs in each consecutive year up to 1866. In 1862 my father sold almost the whole of his flock. So the last few years he has bred very few pure Leicesters, though my brother is gradually working up a good flock.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> You will see that he did not breed such a very great quantity. On an average he let about 70 or 80 tups every year.</p>
<p>Yours very sincerely | Sam Sanday.</p>
<p>P.S. Could you just mention the schedule of our show in your columns the same as you kindly did for us last year.<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p> 
